      "id": "bug-020",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-05T21:30:00+07:00",
      "error_message": "***ERROR*** A stack overflow in task mhi_task has been detected. Boot loop when AC connected.",
      "file": "src/MHI-AC-Ctrl/MHI-AC-Ctrl-core.cpp",
      "root_cause": "STACK_SIZE was 2048 bytes (upstream ESPHome value sized for lightweight ESP_LOG). This project's Log.ln puts a 512-byte buffer on the task stack per call and prints via USB CDC; the first operation-data cycle with a real AC fires several Log.ln calls from mhi_task and overflows the stack. Only reproducible with real AC SPI data - bench builds never entered that code path.",
      "fix": "STACK_SIZE 2048 -> 8192 in MHI-AC-Ctrl-core.cpp. Verified 60s stable on hardware with AC connected, full operation-data cycle running.",
      "tags": [
        "stack-overflow",
        "freertos",
        "mhi-task",
        "logger",
        "hardware-only-bug"
      ],
