      "id": "bug-022",
      "timestamp": "2026-07-05T22:30:00+07:00",
      "error_message": "MQTT commands ignored when no USB host attached; MHICORE 'Missed 1425 frames'",
      "file": "src/main.cpp",
      "root_cause": "ARDUINO_USB_CDC_ON_BOOT=1 makes Serial a USB CDC device; with no host draining, each write blocks up to the CDC tx timeout. Logger writes char-by-char, so log lines blocked the MHI task (missed frames) and starved mqtt_client.loop() so inbound commands never processed. Only reproducible with USB unplugged/unmonitored.",
      "fix": "Serial.setTxTimeoutMs(0) after Serial.begin() in both setup() and safeMode() — drops log output instead of blocking when no host present",
